The paper discusses a methodology for improving multilabel classification using probabilistic binary classifiers and a classifier trained on co-occurrences of labels. This falls under the subfield of machine learning, specifically in the area of classification. The paper also experiments with standard corpora of labeled documents, indicating a focus on natural language processing and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also mentions the use of probabilistic base classifiers, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
